      <Label alignment="CENTER" layoutY="56.0" prefHeight="395.0" prefWidth="717.0" text="1. The purpose of playing Blackjack: Beat the Dealer&#9;&#9;&#10; 1.1. How do you beat the dealer?&#9;&#9;&#10;    1) By drawing a hand value that is higher than the dealer’s hand value   &#9;&#9;&#10;    2) By the dealer drawing a hand value that goes over 21.&#9;&#9;&#10;    3) By drawing a hand value of 21 on your first two cards, when the dealer does not.&#9;&#9;&#10; 1.2. How do you lose to the dealer?&#9;&#9;&#10;    1) Your hand value exceeds 21.&#9;&#9;&#10;    2) The dealers hand has a greater value than yours at the end of the round.&#9;&#9;&#10; 1.3 How do you find a hand’s total value?&#9;&#9;&#10;    1) 2 through 10 count at face value, i.e. a 2 counts as two, a 9 counts as nine.&#9;&#9;&#10;    2) Face cards (J,Q,K) count as 10.&#9;&#9;&#10;    3) Ace can count as a 1 or an 11 depending on which value helps the hand the most.&#9;&#9;&#10;2. Playing Blackjack&#9;&#9;&#10;    1) Stand: If your first two cards are acceptable, stand and the next player moves to the dealer.&#9;&#9;&#10;    2) Hit: If you would like more cards to improve your hand total, the dealer will deal you more cards,&#10;              one at a time, until you either “bust” (go over 21) or you choose to stand. There is no limit on the &#10;              number of cards you can take (other than going over a total of 21).&#9;&#9;&#10;    3) Resign: resign the game.&#9;&#9;&#10;    4) Help: You can check how to play Blackjack" textFill="#d2f2b1">
